20:
Sir Light! For a champion to take
notice of me, I...
It's more than I deserve.
25:
Whoa... Look at that. Someone's
treating you like a champion for once.
29: I am paying him his due respect.
32: I suggest you try it sometime, Alk.
39:
Sir Light is a hero, who sacrificed
everything to defend his land. Though
you may come from a different place,
as your better, he is owed—
53: We are all comrades, Yuwel. Equals.
56:
If anything, I should be grateful they
took me in, powerless as I am...
59:
Ahem! What I mean to say is, do not
stand on ceremony.
Address me as Alk does.
60:
Now, I've taken enough of your time.
I will leave you to your training.
64:
Can I ask why you look up to
Light so much?
67:
Because he's a champion!
Because even without power,
he seeks to protect.
72: Huh? When? We all just met.
76: I was lost, alone in the dark.
83:
I'm not being figurative.
I was in a place WITH NO LIGHT.
85:
I had just been attacked in the
Kaleidoscope. Shadows began closing
in around me, and I...
I lost the will to fight.
87:
But then I saw a faint glow.
It was no brighter than a candle,
but it was enough.
89:
When I drew closer,
I saw something strange.
The glow had two ears and a tail.
95:
I followed that gleam like a stray ship
after a beacon. I lost all track of time,
but at last I reached...
98:
Starview Village...
And, come to think of it, Light was the
first one to find you.
101:
Yes. I know it all seems outlandish—
like a dream... But I truly believe that
Light guided me here.
104: Mm... Yeah, I think he did too.
111:
Yep. 'Cause he also changed
my world. Ever since Light arrived
at Starview, nothing's been the same
—for either me or Stella.
113:
I mean, I don't idolize him like you do,
and there are times I think he's 
a boring stick in the mud.
But I can tell—he's the real deal.
116:
Hey, what kind of champion do you
think he was? Like, what do you think
he looked like?
119:
I'm certain he looked just like
a champion from legend—
a fair and stalwart young knight.
122:
I'm not too sure about that. What if he
was super buff and burly, like a bear?
125:
With half his face buried in a great
beard? Heh... Well, I'd be intimidated—
that's for sure.
129:
Haha. Same... But no matter how Light
used to look, I want to help him
change back.
132:
On that, we agree. But, well, we won't
be much use as we are now.
135:
Fair. You, uh...
want to start training together?
138:
Yes... I think having a sparring partner
WOULD help. That is, if you can
keep up with me.
141:
Oh please. I can take you. ...As long as
you don't get, you know... TOO serious.
